Description: Floor sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) black-figured pottery open vessel; outside reserved; interior: cream slip; part of a bull to right; red patch on neck; filling ornament: dots; incision used for details of bull; inscription cut on the outside.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 21.2.11)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.963)
